candidates.description: Set from which the Exponential mechanism will return an element.

lower.description: Estimated minimum possible value of the statistic. Only useful for the snapping mechanism.

upper.description: Estimated maximum possible value of the statistic. Only useful for the snapping mechanism.

name: dp_minimum

mechanism.description: Privatizing mechanism to use. One of [`Exponential`, `Laplace`, `Snapping`, `Gaussian`, `AnalyticGaussian`]

privacy_usage.description: Object describing the type and amount of privacy to be used for the mechanism release.

return.description: Differentially private estimates of the minimum elements of the data.

description: Returns differentially private estimates of the minimum elements of each column of the data.
